  "conditionals": 95,
  "description": "Peptidoglycan biosynthesis in Escherichia coli is the essential process of bacterial cell wall synthesis, involving cytoplasmic synthesis of UDP-NAM-pentapeptide precursors, membrane-localized lipid II assembly, and periplasmic transglycosylation and transpeptidation by penicillin-binding proteins (PBPs). This pathway is the primary target of \u03b2-lactam antibiotics and is essential for cell shape determination, osmotic protection, and cell division.",
  "id": "ecoli_peptidoglycan_biosynthesis",
  "logicGates": {
    "and": 2,
    "not": 4,
    "or": 7
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    A[Cell Growth] --> B[Need for Cell Wall]\n    C[Cell Division Initiated] --> D[Septum Formation Signal]\n    \n    B --> E{OR: Growth or<br/>Division?}\n    D --> E\n    \n    E -->|Lateral Growth| F[Activate PG Synthesis]\n    E -->|Septal Growth| G[Activate Septal PG]\n    \n    F --> H[Cytoplasmic Precursor Synthesis]\n    H --> I[UDP-GlcNAc from Glucose]\n    I --> J[\"MurA: UDP-GlcNAc + PEP\"]\n    J --> K[UDP-GlcNAc-enolpyruvate]\n    K --> L[MurB Reduction]\n    L --> M(\\1)\n    \n    M --> N[\"MurC: Add L-Alanine\"]\n    N --> O[UDP-MurNAc-L-Ala]\n    O --> P[\"MurD: Add D-Glutamate\"]\n    P --> Q[UDP-MurNAc-L-Ala-D-Glu]\n    \n    Q --> R[\"MurE: Add meso-DAP\"]\n    R --> S[UDP-MurNAc-tripeptide]\n    S --> T[\"MurF: Add D-Ala-D-Ala\"]\n    T --> U[UDP-MurNAc-pentapeptide]\n    \n    U --> V[Cytoplasmic Precursor Complete]\n    V --> W[\"MraY: Transfer to Undecaprenyl-P\"]\n    W --> X[Lipid I at Membrane]\n    \n    X --> Y[\"MurG: Add GlcNAc\"]\n    Y --> Z[Lipid II Formation]\n    Z --> AA[GlcNAc-MurNAc-pentapeptide]\n    \n    AA --> AB{AND: Lipid II +<br/>Flippase?}\n    Z --> AC[FtsW/RodA Flippase]\n    AC --> AB\n    \n    AB -->|Yes| AD[Lipid II Translocation]\n    AD --> AE[Periplasmic Face of Membrane]\n    \n    AE --> AF{OR: Lateral or<br/>Septal?}\n    AF -->|Lateral| AG[RodA-PBP2 Complex]\n    AF -->|Septal| AH[FtsW-PBP3/FtsI Complex]\n    \n    AG --> AI[Lateral Wall Synthesis]\n    AH --> AJ[Septal Wall Synthesis]\n    \n    AI --> AK[Transglycosylase Activity]\n    AJ --> AK\n    \n    AK --> AL[PBP1a/PBP1b Bifunctional]\n    AL --> AM[Glycan Chain Polymerization]\n    AM --> AN[\u03b2-1,4 Glycosidic Bonds]\n    AN --> AO[Extend Glycan Strand]\n    \n    AO --> AP{AND: Glycan Extended +<br/>Adjacent Strands?}\n    AP -->|Yes| AQ[Transpeptidase Activity]\n    \n    AQ --> AR[PBP2 or PBP3 Transpeptidase]\n    AR --> AS[Cross-Link Formation]\n    AS --> AT[D-Ala at Position 4]\n    AT --> AU[meso-DAP at Position 3]\n    AU --> AV[Peptide Bond 4\u21923]\n    AV --> AW[Release Terminal D-Ala]\n    \n    AW --> AX[Cross-Linked Peptidoglycan]\n    AX --> AY[3D Mesh Network]\n    AY --> AZ[Cell Wall Strength]\n    \n    AZ --> BA[Osmotic Protection]\n    BA --> BB[Cell Shape Maintenance]\n    \n    F --> BC[MreB Cytoskeleton]\n    BC --> BD[Direct Lateral PG Synthesis]\n    BD --> BE[/Rod Shape Determination/]\n    \n    G --> BF[FtsZ Ring Formation]\n    BF --> BG[Z-Ring at Midcell]\n    BG --> BH[Recruit Division Machinery]\n    BH --> BI[FtsQLB Complex]\n    BI --> AH\n    \n    AS --> BJ{\u03b2-Lactam<br/>Antibiotic Present?}\n    BJ -->|Yes| BK[/PBP Inhibition/]\n    BK --> BL[/Block Transpeptidation/]\n    BL --> BM[Weakened Cell Wall]\n    BM --> BN[Cell Lysis]\n    \n    BJ -->|No| AW\n    \n    AX --> BO[Cell Wall Recycling]\n    BO --> BP[Lytic Transglycosylases]\n    BP --> BQ[Cleave Glycan Strands]\n    BQ --> BR[Anhydro-MurNAc Products]\n    BR --> BS[Import to Cytoplasm]\n    BS --> BT[AmpG Permease]\n    BT --> BU[Recycle NAM-peptides]\n    BU --> V\n    \n    BB --> BV{Cell<br/>Elongated?}\n    BV -->|Yes| BW[Proceed to Division]\n    BV -->|No| F\n    \n    BW --> BX[Septal PG Synthesis]\n    BX --> AJ\n    AJ --> BY[Septum Closure]\n    BY --> BZ[Two Daughter Cells]\n    \n    AX --> CA[Quality Control]\n    CA --> CB{Proper<br/>Cross-Linking?}\n    CB -->|Yes| AZ\n    CB -->|No| CC[Activate Autolysins]\n    CC --> CD[/Localized PG Degradation/]\n    CD --> CE[Remodel Cell Wall]\n    CE --> F\n    \n    M --> CF{OR: Alternative<br/>Substrate?}\n    CF -->|Minor| CG[Lipid II Variants]\n    CF -->|Major| N\n    \n    AS --> CH[Different PBP Specificity]\n    CH --> CI{PBP Type?}\n    CI -->|High MW| AR\n    CI -->|Low MW| CJ[PBP4/5/6 Carboxypeptidase]\n    CJ --> CK[Trim Pentapeptide to Tetrapeptide]\n    CK --> CL[Regulate Cross-Linking Degree]\n    \n    AY --> CM[~30% Cross-Linked in E. coli]\n    CM --> CN[Balance Rigidity and Flexibility]\n    \n    BZ --> C